      "locator": {
        "source_id": "rcog-chronic-pelvic-pain-gtg41-2012",
        "page_number": 3,
        "section_heading": "Page 3",
        "paragraph_or_text_span": "Careful scrutiny of the woman’s history and physical findings will frequently reveal factors that may be contributing to the pain and can therefore be at least partially treated. Given the incomplete understanding of the genesis of pelvic pain, it may be necessary to keep an open mind about the cause and consider unusual diagnoses, such as hernias or retroperitoneal tumours, or consider causes whi",
